    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="259"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee/704: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 15, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>313. Your 335, December 15, 11 a.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d259fn67">Not
                        printed.</note> Dodd has telegraphed summary of original Hitler proposals
                    and Lindsay, in <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi> dated December 8,<note
                        n="68" xml:id="d259fn68">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_328">p. 328</ref>.</note> has
                    furnished us with British reply requesting further clarification.</p>
                <p>Cable brief summary of subsequent correspondence, together with your analysis of
                    British Government’s present policy and objectives.</p>
                <p>Mail cipher text to Berlin and Geneva.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
